        {
            "type": "h2-post",
            "content": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "The <b><i>Präteritum</i></b>, also known as the simple past tense, is used in German to describe actions that happened in the past and are considered completed. It is particularly <b>common in written narratives</b>, such as stories, reports, and historical accounts. In spoken German, the Präteritum is less frequently used in everyday conversation, where the Perfekt tense is often preferred, especially with regular verbs. However, it is essential to learn and understand the Präteritum as it remains prominent in written German and with certain commonly used verbs."
        },
        {
            "type": "callout",
            "content": "If you are a beginner, you just need to learn the präteritum of a few verbs. You will slowly learn other verbs as your level increases."
        },
        {
            "type": "h2",
            "content": "Usage"
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "We use the <i>Präteritum</i> tense to express:"
        },
        {
            "type": "list",
            "itemsList": {
                "items": [
                    {
                        "text": "<b>Narratives and Written Texts:</b> The Präteritum is widely used in novels, newspapers, and historical texts.",
                        "example": {
                            "audio": "Er ging in die Stadt und kaufte ein Buch.",
                            "text": "Example: Er $__ging-gehen[verb-link-hover]__$ in die Stadt und kaufte ein Buch.",
                            "translation": "(He went to the city and bought a book.)"
                        }
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "<b>Formal Speech:</b> Sometimes used in formal or literary speech.",
                        "example": {
                            "audio": "Gestern fand die Versammlung statt.",
                            "text": "Gestern $__fand-finden[verb-link-hover]__$ die Versammlung statt.",
                            "translation": "(The meeting took place yesterday.)"
                        }
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "<b>Certain Verbs in Spoken Language:</b> Some verbs, particularly modal verbs and a few other common verbs (e.g., sein, haben, werden), are normally used in the <i>Präteritum</i> tense in spoken German rather than their <i>Perfekt</i> tense.",
                        "example": {
                            "audio": "Ich war müde.",
                            "text": "Ich $__war-sein[verb-link-hover]__$ müde.",
                            "translation": "(I was tired.)"
                        }
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
