        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "In German, while the Perfekt tense is generally preferred in spoken language for most verbs, there are several verbs that are commonly used in their <i>Präteritum</i> (simple past) form, even in everyday speech. These verbs tend to be frequently used and are often essential in narrative contexts. The main verbs that are typically used in their Präteritum form rather than their Perfekt form are:"
